Their Names were, Sir Richard Empſon Knight, and Edmund Dudley, both (ſaith Sir Richard Baker, fol. 247.) Lawyers, and both of them Barons of the Exchequer, and Iuſtices of the Peace throughout England: Dudley of a good Family, but Empſon the Son of

a Sieve-maker: So true is that Remark of the Poet;
               Mendico aſperius nihil eſt cum ſurgit ad Altum.
